parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of fuel injectors can cause fuel leaks, leading to engine fires, which can result in serious injury or death.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or incomplete recall repairs can lead to continued safety risks, including engine fires, due to faulty fuel injectors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to notify owners of recalls can lead to continued safety risks, including engine fires, due to faulty fuel injectors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Cooling system failures can cause engine overheating, damage to engine components, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Timing belt failures can cause engine damage, engine stalling, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Turbocharger failures can cause loss of power, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Engine compartment fires can cause damage to the vehicle, injury to occupants, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: smoke or flames visible under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine mount failures can cause vibration, noise, and potentially lead to engine damage, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Exhaust system failures can cause decreased engine performance, noise, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The failure of the electrical system wiring can cause a range of issues, including faulty alternator operation, battery drain, and spark plug malfunction, leading to hesitation upon acceleration, warning lights on the dashboard, and potentially even engine fires.
symptoms: smoke or flames from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the battery to drain, leading to hesitation upon acceleration, warning lights on the dashboard, and potentially even engine fires.
Battery failure can cause hesitation upon acceleration, warning lights on the dashboard, and potentially even engine fires.
Spark plug failure can cause engine misfires, hesitation upon acceleration, and decreased engine performance.
Power amplifier failure can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to hesitation upon acceleration, warning lights on the dashboard, and potentially even engine fires.
Corrosion at the battery cable can cause hesitation upon acceleration, warning lights on the dashboard, and potentially even engine fires.
